name: Buy OTM Call
description: Focuses on bullish trade execution in high volatility

name: Buy OTM Put
description: Focuses on bearish trade execution in high volatility

name: Protective Put
description: Refers to buying futures and puts for protection

name: Call Backspread
description: A strategy designed to capitalize on bullish moves with minimal risk

name: Put Backspread
description: A strategy designed to benefit from bearish moves with limited risk

name: Bull Call spread
description: A strategy used to capitalize on moderate bullish price movement with limited risk

name: Protective Call
description: A strategy designed to protect against downside risk while allowing for upside profit potential

name: Bear Put Spread
description: A strategy used to capitalize on bearish price movement with limited risk

name: Covered Put
description: A strategy used to sell a put option while holding an equivalent amount of the underlying asset as protection

name: Covered Call
description: A strategy where a call option is sold while holding the underlying asset; providing income in exchange for potential upside loss

name: Short Strangle
description: A strategy involving selling both a call and a put option on the same underlying asset with different strike prices

name: Short Straddle
description: A strategy involving selling both a call and a put option at the same strike price to profit from low volatility

name: Long Straddle
description: A strategy involving buying both a call and a put option at the same strike price to profit from significant price movement

name: Long Strangle
description: A strategy involving buying both a call and a put option with different strike prices to profit from large price movements

name: Long Call Ladder
description: A strategy where a long call is purchased; a call option is sold; and a third call option is bought at a higher strike price for risk management

name: Long Put Ladder
description: A strategy where a long put is purchased; a put option is sold; and a third put option is bought at a lower strike price for managing risk

name: Iron Butterfly
description: A strategy involving buying a lower strike put; selling a middle strike put; and selling a middle strike call; while buying a higher strike call to profit from low volatility

name: Call Ratio Spread
description: A strategy that involves buying one call option and selling two call options at a higher strike price to profit from limited upward movement

name: Put Ratio Spread
description: A strategy that involves buying one put option and selling two put options at a lower strike price to profit from moderate bearish movement

name: Strap
description: A strategy involving buying one call and two put options at the same strike price to profit from significant downward movement

name: Strip
description: A strategy involving buying one call and two put options to profit from significant price movement in either direction

name: NF-Dynamic Volatility Manager
description: A strategy that balances option and asset delta to minimize directional risk and profiting from volatility or time decay

name: NF-Dynamic Volatility Manager Hedge
description: A strategy that minimizes directional risk by balancing portfolio delta using long and short options

name: BN-Dynamic Volatility Manager
description: A strategy that balances option and asset delta to minimize directional risk and profiting from volatility or time decay

name: BN-Dynamic Volatility Manager Hedge
description: A strategy that minimizes directional risk by balancing portfolio delta using long and short options
